  "text": "The Grafana datasource plugin query flow begins at the HTTP API handler in pkg/api/ds_query.go:QueryMetricsV2 (lines 68-88), which receives a POST request to /ds/query with a dtos.MetricRequest body. This handler calls hs.queryDataService.QueryData() passing the request.\n\nThe query service implementation in pkg/services/query/query.go:ServiceImpl.QueryData (line 126) delegates to the internal queryData method (line 101), which parses the metric request into parsed queries grouped by datasource. For single datasource queries, it calls handleQuerySingleDatasource (line 288-331), which:\n1) Creates a backend.QueryDataRequest with the queries\n2) Checks if there's a query service client available via qsDatasourceClientBuilder\n3) Falls back to pluginClient.QueryData() for single-tenant flow\n\nThe plugin client call chain begins at pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go:Service.QueryData (line 50-95), which retrieves the plugin from the registry and calls plugin.QueryData(ctx, req). The plugin is a backend.Handler that could be a GRPC plugin or core plugin.\n\nFor GRPC plugins, the implementation is in pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go:ClientV2.QueryData (line 162-190), which:\n1) Converts the backend.QueryDataRequest to a protobuf request using backend.ToProto().QueryDataRequest(req)\n2) Makes a GRPC call to the plugin's DataClient.QueryData() method\n3) Converts the protobuf response back to backend.QueryDataResponse using backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse(protoResp)\n4) Sets RefID on any data frames returned (in manager/client/client.go lines 85-92)\n\nThe response (backend.QueryDataResponse) contains a map of refID to DataResponse, where each DataResponse contains a slice of data frames. The response flows back through the service and API handler to toJsonStreamingResponse (pkg/api/ds_query.go line 90-105).\n\nFinally, the HTTP response is serialized in pkg/api/response/response.go via JSONStreaming (line 199-207) which creates a StreamingResponse. The StreamingResponse.WriteTo method (line 153-168) uses jsoniter to encode the QueryDataResponse to JSON, serializing the data frames as JSON objects in the HTTP response body.\n\nExpression queries bypass the plugin client and instead use pkg/expr/service.go:Service.TransformData (line 68-100) and ExecutePipeline (line 110-125), which return frames via the Values.AsDataFrames method, also flowing through the same JSONStreaming serialization path."
